<span class="smalltext">
2007-02-01 17:53:50&nbsp;<!-- begin conditional display of username -->

PhillipB


<!-- end conditional display of username -->

<!-- csif cond="1" -->
[<!--a href="http://www.oreillynet.com/cs/user/create/cs_msg?x-lr=cs_msg/88903&x-lr2=a/2849" class="smalltext" title="Reply to this message">Reply</a> | --><a href="http://www.oreillynet.com//cs/user/view/cs_msg/88903" class="smalltext">View</a>]</span><br />

<br />
<div class="commenttext">

I use PhotoShopCS and PhotoShopCS2 and this might be similar to Elements. Here is an easy way without outlining the subject for color.<br />
1st - go to "Hue/Saturation"<br />
2nd -  then drag "Saturation" to the far left, then hit enter.<br />
3rd - you now have a new layer (Hue/Saturation). Now, make sure the "black box" on your tool box is on the bottom.<br />
4th - use your "Erasure" tool and drag it over the subject/item you want in color.<br />
Good Luck<br />
PB

</div>
