<a name="id_11647"></a>
<span class="headline">Fill the Frame</span><br />
<span class="smalltext">
2002-11-24 11:49:56&nbsp;<!-- begin conditional display of username -->

anonymous2


<!-- end conditional display of username -->

<!-- csif cond="1" -->
[<!--a href="http://www.oreillynet.com/cs/user/create/cs_msg?x-lr=cs_msg/11647&x-lr2=a/2849" class="smalltext" title="Reply to this message">Reply</a> | --><a href="http://www.oreillynet.com//cs/user/view/cs_msg/11647" class="smalltext">View</a>]</span><br />

<br />
<div class="commenttext">

One of the most important tips is to always try to fill the frame with your subject. Also, look at the corners of the frame to make sure nothing is in the way, such as fingers, doors or other unknown objects.

</div>
</li>

