<a name="id_80670"></a>
<span class="headline">Holding my 5.0 mrega pixels Gate way steady</span><br />
<span class="smalltext">
2006-03-05 11:33:08&nbsp;<!-- begin conditional display of username -->

wjodon


<!-- end conditional display of username -->

<!-- csif cond="1" -->
[<!--a href="http://www.oreillynet.com/cs/user/create/cs_msg?x-lr=cs_msg/80670&x-lr2=a/2849" class="smalltext" title="Reply to this message">Reply</a> | --><a href="http://www.oreillynet.com//cs/user/view/cs_msg/80670" class="smalltext">View</a>]</span><br />

<br />
<div class="commenttext">

Use a monopod, which is much more portable than a tripod and can really help with long exposures.  I use an <strong>Hakuba Mono Stand 10</strong>, which has the virtues of being small and easy to carry in an urban environment, and of doubling as a mini-tripod.

</div>
</li>

